The Federal Executive Council (FEC) has sent good wishes to Vice President Yemi Osinbajo, who is recuperating from a leg surgery in a Lagos hospital. Senior Special Assistant to the President on Media and Publicity, Office of the Vice President, Mr Laolu Akande, on Saturday announced Osinbajo was going in for a surgical procedure. However, in a statement by the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF), Mr Boss Mustapha, on Sunday, FEC wished the Vice President quick recovery.   IPOB demands Senator Bulkachuwa arrest     Fayemi sacks political appointees     JUST IN: Gunmen abduct four travellers in Anambra   “The Federal Executive Council (FEC), wishes the Vice President, Prof Yemi Osinbajo quick recovery following a successful operation on account of a fracture of his right femur (thigh bone), possibly related to a long standing injury associated with the game of squash. “The surgical operation which was performed by a team of specialist doctors in Lagos has been reported to be successful. “As Professor Osinbajo recuperates from the surgical operation, FEC wishes him quick recovery so as to continue to give the needed support for the overall growth and stability of the country,” the statement reads.